<p dir="ltr">But hereâ€™s the thing: If you want to drive substantial returns on your online advertising spend, then achieving <strong>high conversion rates</strong> and <strong>low costs per lead</strong><em>Â has</em> to stay at the top of your mind.</p>
<p>A key step towards driving high conversion rates and low costs per conversion, of course, is defining what those things look like. Whatâ€™s a high Google Ads conversion rate? Whatâ€™s a good Meta Ads cost per lead? And how does conversion rate optimization change depending on what industry youâ€™re in?</p>
<p>These are the questions weâ€™re here to answer. With this guide, our goal is to provide the essential <strong>conversion rate benchmarks</strong> you need to get your conversion rate optimization (CRO) efforts off to the right start.</p>
