<div id="average-google-ads-cost-per-conversion-by-industry"></div>
<h2>How much does a Google Ads conversion cost?</h2>
<p><strong>The average cost per lead across Google Ads is $70.11.</strong></p>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/2025-GA-Benchmarks-CPL-871x1024.webp" alt="2025 google ads benchmarks - cost per lead" width="871" height="1024" class="aligncenter wp-image-91516 size-large" /></div>
<p>Taking a look at the industries with the highest average costs per leadâ€”Attorneys &amp; Legal Services at $131.63, Furniture at $121.51, and Business Services at $103.54â€”we see a common theme: A <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/01/26/sales-cycle">longer sales cycle</a>. In other words, if youâ€™re marketing a product or service that people typically take a long time to mull over (e.g., a laptop, legal advice, etc.), you can expect to spend more money for each conversion you drive.</p>
<p>At the other end of the spectrum, inspiring prospects to take valuable actions isnâ€™t quite as expensive in industries like Restaurants &amp; Food, and Arts &amp; Entertainment, both with a CPL of $30.27, and Animals &amp; Pets with a CPL of $31.82. In the case of Automotive&#8211;Repair, Service &amp; Parts, with an average CPL of $28.50, which youâ€™d typically expect to be one with long sales cycles, the below-average cost per conversion is likely due (in part) to the sense of urgency people feel when it comes to issues with their cars.</p>
