<p>This proactive approach is a sales revival tactic, effectively wooing customers back for a satisfying return purchase. Complementing this with razor-sharp site analytics and on-point onsite searches means rolling out the red carpet straight to checkout.</p>
<p>And let&#8217;s not forget the crowd-pleasers: <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/02/06/personalized-marketing">personalized</a> product suggestions, tempting promotions, and the persuasive power of ratings and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/09/16/get-more-google-reviews">reviews</a> act like the supportive best friends of conversion, turning browsers into buyers by making them feel like the VIPs of your online storefront.</p>
<h3>5. User-generated content is a conversion catalyst</h3>
<p>Analysis of 1,200 websites showed a solid <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/1388280/ugc-impacts-conversion-rates/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">3.2%</a> conversion rate with the presence of UGC, and that rate jumped by an additional 3.8% when visitors encountered and scrolled through UGC.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/conversion-rate-optimization-statistics-wordstream-indicator.webp" alt="conversion rate optimization - chart showing indicators of high conversion rate" width="936" height="569" class="aligncenter wp-image-80069 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/conversion-rate-optimization-statistics-wordstream-indicator.webp 936w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/conversion-rate-optimization-statistics-wordstream-indicator-480x292.webp 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 936px, 100vw" /></p>
