<h3>9. The majority of websites maintain a sub-40% bounce rate</h3>
<p>When it comes to keeping visitors hooked, it seems like two-thirds of websites are sticking the landing, boasting an average bounce rate below the <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/website/web-traffic-analytics-report">40%</a> mark.</p>
<p>On the flip side, only a small fraction, about 11%, find themselves on the higher end of the spectrum, with <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2016/04/07/reduce-bounce-rate">bounce rates</a> soaring over 60%. This stat highlights that most sites are good at enticing visitors to stick around and explore more than just the landing page.</p>
