<div id="troubleshoot"></div>
<h2>Google Ads conversion tracking troubleshooting</h2>
<p><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/21/google-ads-not-converting">Not seeing any conversions in your Google Ads</a>? If issues arise with your Google Ads conversion tracking, check out these tips and be sure to read our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/24/google-ads-conversion-tracking">post on conversion tracking hangups</a>. Be sure also to visit our post on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/02/08/google-ads-conversion-tracking-mistakes">conversion tracking mistakes to avoid</a>, since these ones are sneaky and can go undetected.</p>
<h3>Conversion columns arenâ€™t showing any data</h3>
<p>It can take up to 24 hours for conversion data to start appearing in Google Ads. If after 24 hours conversions still arenâ€™t showing up, itâ€™s possible that no customers have converted yet. One way to test this is by going through the motions of a conversion yourself by clicking on your ad when it appears, and doing whatever action is required to trigger the conversion on your site. If after another 24 hours your conversion isnâ€™t registering, double-check that the code was installed correctly. You might have to install additional plug-ins or move the code to a different part of the page.</p>
<h3>Campaign receives many clicks, but few conversions</h3>
<p>Campaigns receiving many clicks and few conversions causes<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/cost-per-action"> higher cost per conversion</a> which lowers your return on investment (ROI). To understand why this may be happening, ask yourself:</p>
<ul>
<li>Are you using a dedicated <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/great-landing-pages">landing page</a>? Sending users to your homepage can result in low conversion rates.</li>
<li>Is the landing page optimized for conversion? Is there a prominent CTA, a simple form, and is the key information available above the fold?</li>
<li>Is the landing page relevant to the ad? Does it contain the same keywords and copy so that the person is reassured upon clicking on the ad that theyâ€™ll get what youâ€™ve promised them?</li>
</ul>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/google-ads-conversion-tracking-small-business-landing-page-example.jpg" alt="google ads conversion tracking - conversion optimized landing page example " width="720" height="351" class="aligncenter wp-image-64064 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/google-ads-conversion-tracking-small-business-landing-page-example.jpg 720w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/google-ads-conversion-tracking-small-business-landing-page-example-480x234.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>A landing page from a<a href="https://localiq.com/local-marketing-lab/small-business-websites/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> small business website </a>thatâ€™s optimized for conversions. Find other <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/03/08/landing-page-examples">landing page examples here</a>. </em></p>
<h2>Set up your Google Ads conversion tracking now</h2>
<p>Conversion tracking is essential for any <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/02/10/paid-media-strategy">successful paid media strategy</a>, so taking the time to set up conversion tracking is well worth it. If you feel your conversion tracking is already in a good place but want to explore your account performance further, check out our free <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader">Google Ads Grader</a> to get more optimization insights.</p>
